---
import { BRAND } from "astro:schema";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Mobile App Development Services | GeneralSoft UAE"
  description="Professional mobile app development services for iOS, Android, and cross-platform solutions in the UAE."
  path="/services/mobile-apps/"
  image="/img/og-mobile-apps.jpg"
>
  <section class="service-content" id="mobile-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Mobile App Development Services</h2>
      <p>
        In the UAE's competitive digital market, a website is rarely just an
        online brochure — it is often the primary point of contact between a
        business and its customers, the destination of paid advertising spend,
        the surface through which trust is established or lost, and
        increasingly, the channel through which transactions happen. A website
        that loads slowly, looks generic, or fails to communicate a clear value
        proposition costs real money in lost leads and conversions.
      </p>
      <p>
        At GeneralSoft, web development is approached as an engineering and
        design discipline simultaneously. We build websites and web applications
        using modern, performance-first frameworks — primarily React, Next.js,
        and Astro — with a focus on Core Web Vitals scores that satisfy both
        users and search engines. Visually, we design for clarity and
        credibility: layouts that communicate trust immediately, information
        hierarchies that guide visitors to the actions that matter, and brand
        expression that differentiates rather than blends in.
      </p>
      <p>
        The web and network combination reflects a practical reality for many of
        our clients: the performance of a website or web application is
        inseparable from the network infrastructure it runs on and connects to.
        A beautifully built web application that sits behind a poorly configured
        network, a CDN that isn't properly tuned, or an office network that
        can't support the team using it is still a slow, unreliable experience.
        We address both layers together, which is why clients working on office
        expansions, data center migrations, or cloud deployments often engage us
        for both the application and the network design.
      </p>
      <p>
        For businesses in UAE free zones and corporate districts — where office
        infrastructure often needs to be set up from scratch and must support
        VoIP, video conferencing, cloud access, and secure remote work
        simultaneously — our network design service provides a single point of
        accountability for the entire connected environment.
      </p>

      <h3>Native iOS Development</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>iPhone Apps</h4><p>
            Beautiful, high-performance iOS apps built with Swift and SwiftUI
            following Apple's Human Interface Guidelines.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>iPad Apps</h4><p>
            Optimized iPad experiences with multitasking, split view, and Apple
            Pencil support.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Apple Watch Apps</h4><p>
            Wearable experiences that extend your iOS app with complications,
            notifications, and health tracking.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>App Store Optimization</h4><p>
            Expert guidance on App Store submission, optimization, and download
            growth strategies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Native Android Development</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Kotlin Development:</strong> Modern, concise Android apps using
          Kotlin and Jetpack Compose
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Material Design:</strong> Beautiful interfaces following Google's
          Material Design 3 guidelines
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tablet Optimization:</strong> Responsive layouts that adapt to different
          screen sizes and foldables
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Wear OS Apps:</strong> Smartwatch applications for Android wearable
          devices
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Cross-Platform Development</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>React Native</h4><p>
            Build once, deploy on iOS and Android with native performance using
            React Native and JavaScript.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Flutter</h4><p>
            Beautiful natively compiled apps with Flutter's rich widget library
            and hot reload.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Progressive Web Apps</h4><p>
            Web applications that behave like native apps with offline support,
            notifications, and home screen installation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Cost-Effective Solutions</h4><p>
            Reduce development time and cost by maintaining a single codebase
            for multiple platforms.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Types of Mobile Apps We Build</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>E-commerce Apps:</strong> Shopping apps with product catalogs, cart,
          payment integration, and order tracking
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Social Networking:</strong> Community platforms with messaging,
          feeds, profiles, and content sharing
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>On-Demand Services:</strong> Uber-like apps for ride-sharing, food
          delivery, and service marketplaces
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Healthcare Apps:</strong> Telemedicine, fitness tracking, appointment
          booking, and health monitoring
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Education Apps:</strong> E-learning platforms, course delivery,
          quizzes, and progress tracking
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Finance & Banking:</strong> Mobile banking, payment apps, and investment
          platforms
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Mobile App Security</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Secure Authentication:</strong> Biometric authentication, OAuth
          2.0, JWT tokens, and MFA
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Data Encryption:</strong> End-to-end encryption for sensitive data
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>API Security:</strong> Secure communication with SSL pinning and
          request signing
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Secure Storage:</strong> Encrypted local storage using Keychain
          (iOS) and KeyStore (Android)
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Mobile Tech Stack</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>iOS:</strong> Swift, SwiftUI, UIKit, Combine, Core Data, CloudKit
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Android:</strong> Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, Android SDK, Room, WorkManager
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cross-Platform:</strong> React Native, Flutter, Dart, JavaScript/TypeScript
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js, Firebase, AWS Amplify, GraphQL, REST
          APIs
        </li>
        <li><strong>Design:</strong> Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD</li>
        <li><strong>Testing:</strong> XCTest, Espresso, Jest, Detox, Appium</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about our custom software development process in the
          UAE.
        </p>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary
              >Should I build a native app or a cross-platform app?</summary
            >
            <p>
              It depends on your requirements. Native iOS and Android
              development (Swift/Kotlin) delivers the highest performance, best
              platform integration, and most polished experience — but requires
              maintaining two separate codebases. Cross-platform frameworks like
              Flutter and React Native let you share most of your codebase
              across both platforms, reducing cost and development time with
              minimal compromise on performance. For most business applications,
              cross-platform is an excellent choice. For highly
              performance-sensitive or hardware-dependent apps, native
              development is worth the investment.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How long does it take to build a mobile app?</summary>
            <p>
              A focused app with a defined scope — for example, a service
              booking app or an internal operations tool — typically takes eight
              to fourteen weeks from wire-framing to App Store submission.
              Feature-rich consumer apps with back-end infrastructure, payment
              integration, and real-time data can take four to six months. We
              provide a detailed timeline after the discovery and scoping phase.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary
              >How much does mobile app development cost in the UAE?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Cost depends on complexity, platform choice, and back-end
              requirements. A straightforward single-platform app starts from
              AED 35,000–50,000. Multi-platform apps with custom back-ends,
              payment gateways, and third-party integrations typically range
              from AED 80,000–200,000+. We provide a detailed proposal after
              understanding your requirements.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can you build an app that works offline?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes. We design offline-first architectures as a standard
              consideration for apps that may be used in variable-connectivity
              environments — common in logistics, field service, and industrial
              applications. Data syncs automatically when connectivity is
              restored, and the user experience remains functional throughout.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can you update and maintain the app after launch?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes — and this is an important part of the engagement. Mobile
              operating systems update regularly, and apps that aren't
              maintained fall behind on performance, security, and
              compatibility. We offer ongoing maintenance retainers covering OS
              compatibility updates, security patches, performance monitoring,
              and new feature development.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary
              >Do you handle App Store and Google Play submission?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Yes. We manage the full submission process for both the Apple App
              Store and Google Play, including compliance with store guidelines,
              metadata optimization, screenshot preparation, and responding to
              any review feedback from Apple or Google.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

